trend_summary: Across the series the landscape stays dominantly pastoral-wooded. Only scattered new houses and sheds appear along county roads, chiefly near the southwest village, lifting built-up cover slightly yet still sparse. Some pasture blocks are enlarged, a few woodlots cleared or allowed to regrow, and minor road realignments occur; no major industrial or commercial growth.
notable_changes: Incremental roadside housing infill, particularly around the southwest settlement core.
Minor extension and surfacing of local road network connecting dispersed farms.
Enlargement of central-north pasture fields through hedgerow and tree removal.
Patchy forest regrowth on previously cleared southeastern slopes.
